    <h2>How does the site work?</h2>
    <p>MMP360 walks you through the steps to collect the information required to populate the Iowa MMP forms. MMP360 provides a simple map interface to identify feeding operation locations and define the fields to be analyzed in the plan. Text entry and selection boxes are provided for easy data entry. You can register for an account and complete the steps to assemble the mandatory information for free.</p>
    <p>Steps to complete an Iowa MMP using MMP360:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Information about the feeding operation is collected.</li>
      <li>Each field used in the plan is entered into the system with its associated management practices.</li>
      <li>The data inputs are cross-checked for completeness and potential errors.</li>
      <li>The user can run the analyses and generate the MMP forms.</li>
    </ol>
